ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[According to the above information, 11 Vietnamese provinces are
currently infected.
We are grateful to Dr. Richard Rubira from the Disease Preparedness
and International Office of the Chief Veterinary Officer, Canberra,
Australia for bringing to our attention the FMD reports from the 8
member-countries of OIE's Southeast Asia (SEA) Regional Office, available at
<http://www.seafmd-rcu.oie.int/fmd_se_asia.php>.
Viet Nam's table-form report for the last updated month, namely
October 2006, is available at
<http://www.seafmd-rcu.oie.int/fmd_se_asia.php?reptype=table&state=VNM&month=10&year=2006>.
It appears that all outbreaks in Viet Nam during October 2006 were
caused by FMDV serotype O. The website includes maps showing the
location of all reported outbreaks. - Mod.AS]
